u2019s technical and stress\u2011management strengths outweigh his communication style concerns, which appear less debilitating than the explicit communication deficits of C or the interpersonal/health concerns of A and D.\n**Remaining uncertainty**\n- No explicit data on B\u2019s numeric memory or detailed crew\u2011coordination performance; if such a gap exists, it could affect navigation tasks.\n- Lack of concrete evidence on B\u2019s teamwork beyond the negative tone remarks; positive teamwork data from other agents could shift the balance.\n**What would change my vote**\n- If another agent provides strong, explicit evidence of superior teamwork/communication for A or D (e.g., proven crew leadership, calmness under pressure) that outweighs B\u2019s communication flaws.\n- If evidence emerges that B has a critical hidden weakness (e.g., poor numeric memory, severe cockpit\u2011procedural errors).\nGiven the current evidence, Candidate\u202fB appears the most balanced for safe, reliable long\u2011distance operations.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}", "thoughts": "We need to produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON. We must follow instructions: Provide current preferred candidate, summarize evidence, etc. We have our own info: candidate attributes list. Also we have info from other agents (Agent 1 and Agent 2) from their public responses. Let's recap:\n\nAgent 1's public response gave info about D: no explicit calmness, but \"responds to unexpected events adequately\". No explicit teamwork. For B: no explicit teamwork, but \"can be uncooperative\" and \"grumpy\". So we have that.\n\nAgent 2's public response gave info about A: no explicit teamwork, but \"very good leadership qualities\", \"unfriendly\", \"eats unhealthily\". D: no explicit teamwork, but \"responds to unexpected events adequately\", \"concentrates\", \"solves problems\", \"takes responsibility\", \"moody\", \"loner\". B: no weak memory, but \"very conscientious\"